sentences: Bedouine released her third full-length album, Waysides on October 22, 2021.
The album was announced August 18, 2021 with the single "The Wave", which was written about the death of Bedouine's close friend and her resulting grief.
Korkejian did not write new material for the album, instead she selected and finished tracks from among her old demos, the oldest dating back 15 years, the newest from 2017.

Azniv Korkejian, known by her stage name Bedouine (born July 16), is a Syrian-American musician.

The record includes sounds from her memories of her grandmother's home in Syria, specifically on "Summer Cold" and a song written in Armenian "Louise" (which translates to "light” and is written as Լոյս in Armenian).
It is a soundtrack to Spring blossom, to warm air on skin, to the concept of possibility.
